<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-27T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/255: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">House</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-27T11:00:00+00:00">November 27, 1918—11
                                    a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 27—9:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>184. Secret for the President. I have talked the matter over with
                                <persName corresp="#p_BAWS1">Admiral Benson</persName> and I suggest
                            that you take the southern route and land at Marseille. At this time of
                            year the chances are very much in favor of your having far milder and
                            more pleasant weather on the southern route than on the northern one.
                            That was our experience last year. <persName corresp="#p_BAWS1">Benson</persName> tells me that it will only take 2 days longer and
                            that if you sail on the 4th you would arrive at Marseille on the 14th.
                            This would bring you to Paris in plenty of time for the Conference. Will
                            not you please let me know what you decide [to] do.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>